Explanation:

We use a hash map (unordered_map) to store the frequency of each character in the string. Then, we iterate through the string and find the index with the minimum difference between its frequency and the frequency of 'a'. If we find such an index, we return true; otherwise, we return false. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and a space complexity of O(n) due to the hash map usage.

